Issue.Description:
I inherited some code that uses a modified version of InterpolatedValue.cs, that has a method Await( ). Every time I import the toolkit, I have to re-add this method, and I'm not sure how to get rid of calling that method in the code I inherited. Could be by any chance add this method to InterpolatedValue.cs on the grounds it might be useful?

here is the code:

        /// <summary>
        /// Waits for the interpolator to complete, unless cancelled.
        /// The token won't cancel the execution of the interpoloatr
        /// </summary>
        /// <param name="token"></param>
        /// <returns></returns>
        public CoroutineEx Await(CancellationToken token)
        {
            return CoroutineEx.Run(Awaiter(), token);
        }

        private IEnumerator<Yield> Awaiter()
        {
            while (IsRunning)
            {
                yield return Yield.WaitForNextFrame;
            }
        }

